WEBVTT

00:05.092 --> 00:05.309
.

00:05.353 --> 00:08.051
- These guys shot three kids
like it was nothing.

00:08.095 --> 00:09.487
- [groans]

00:09.531 --> 00:10.749
[gun shots]
No, no, please!

00:10.793 --> 00:12.534
I have a daughter.

00:12.577 --> 00:14.623
[intense music]

00:14.666 --> 00:17.234
- What do you think
they're doing to Kim right now?

00:17.278 --> 00:18.583
♪

00:18.627 --> 00:20.237
- Where's Roy Walton?

00:20.281 --> 00:23.153
- Roy tortured
and killed Miller's son.

00:23.197 --> 00:24.589
- You find him.

00:24.633 --> 00:27.070
♪

00:27.114 --> 00:29.072
- You need to be there
for Makayla.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.552
That little girl's
gonna need you.

00:33.424 --> 00:34.817
- [groans]

00:34.860 --> 00:37.080
- You see that?
Kim!

00:37.124 --> 00:39.082
We're taking her to Med.

00:39.126 --> 00:41.258
- We're bringing him in,
Sarge.

00:41.302 --> 00:43.521
- You knew what to expect
when you came here.

00:43.565 --> 00:45.175
Where is Kim Burgess?

00:45.219 --> 00:47.569
- I still ain't
gonna do no talking.

00:47.612 --> 00:49.353
- This is what it feels like.

00:49.397 --> 00:50.833
- I'm not you, Sarge.

00:50.876 --> 00:53.183
- Okay, we'll bring him in.

00:53.227 --> 00:55.577
- Drop his weapon.

00:55.620 --> 00:57.057
- You gotta go home now.

00:57.100 --> 00:59.450
- Did you and Voight
find any leads?

00:59.494 --> 01:01.452
- I love you, Jay.

01:01.496 --> 01:05.630
♪

01:05.674 --> 01:08.068
Maybe we should get married?

01:08.111 --> 01:11.071
- What?
Really?

01:11.114 --> 01:14.813
- I don't want
to be without you.

01:14.857 --> 01:18.078
- Hailey, I don't want to
be without you.

01:18.121 --> 01:21.298
That doesn't mean--
- I love you...

01:21.342 --> 01:22.734
more than anything.

01:22.778 --> 01:25.520
I want to start a new chapter,

01:25.563 --> 01:29.219
a better chapter...

01:29.263 --> 01:31.395
with you.

01:31.439 --> 01:34.398
[phone buzzes]

01:34.442 --> 01:38.228
[soft tense music]

01:38.272 --> 01:40.535
- We--we really got to
get to the hospital.

01:40.578 --> 01:42.537
Um...

01:42.580 --> 01:44.756
- Right.

01:44.800 --> 01:49.761
♪

01:49.805 --> 01:52.764
I'm gonna take
a quick shower, okay?

01:52.808 --> 01:55.767
- Okay.

01:55.811 --> 02:02.861
♪

02:09.216 --> 02:12.175
[dramatic music intensifies]

02:12.219 --> 02:19.269
♪

02:51.867 --> 02:54.522
- [sighs]

02:58.265 --> 03:01.877
- Man, it took me forever
to find a babysitter.

03:01.920 --> 03:04.793
- She's not out of surgery.

03:04.836 --> 03:06.534
- Well, what about the son
of a bitch who shot her?

03:06.577 --> 03:10.407
That Roy?
We grab him up?

03:10.451 --> 03:12.496
- He's still in the wind.

03:12.540 --> 03:14.498
- [sighs]

03:14.542 --> 03:21.549
♪

03:22.898 --> 03:25.770
- Hey, we know anything?

03:37.434 --> 03:39.480
- All right.

03:39.523 --> 03:41.351
She made it through surgery.

03:41.395 --> 03:43.353
- Okay, so she's all right.

03:43.397 --> 03:45.268
- She's in stable condition
at the moment,

03:45.312 --> 03:46.704
but she suffered
extensive injuries.

03:46.748 --> 03:48.837
There's considerable
internal trauma,

03:48.880 --> 03:50.969
so we all just need to wait...
- No, no, no.

03:51.013 --> 03:52.493
- See how her body reacts.
- What the hell does that mean?

03:52.536 --> 03:53.842
- Hey, hey, Adam.
- No.

03:53.885 --> 03:55.278
What the hell does that mean?
You gotta tell me.

03:55.322 --> 03:56.801
Is she gonna make it or not?

03:56.845 --> 03:59.282
- She's stable for now.
We're doing everything we can.

03:59.326 --> 04:00.414
- You and I both know that

04:00.457 --> 04:01.632
that's not the best
that you can do.

04:01.676 --> 04:03.504
All right, we need
more details.

04:03.547 --> 04:05.636
What are we talking about here?
Is it a 50-50 chance?

04:05.680 --> 04:07.334
Better?
Worse?

04:07.377 --> 04:08.900
- It's not productive to
make predictions.

04:08.944 --> 04:11.294
Like I said,
we're doing everything we can.

04:11.338 --> 04:18.345
♪

04:24.829 --> 04:27.789
- Hey, Sam.
- How's she doing?

04:27.832 --> 04:30.487
- Hoping for the best.

04:30.531 --> 04:33.447
- What's the update on Roy?

04:33.490 --> 04:34.665
- There isn't one.

04:34.709 --> 04:36.276
- I can't take my foot off
this one.

04:36.319 --> 04:37.929
Roy did to my son--
I can't--

04:37.973 --> 04:39.757
I won't be able to breathe
until he's in custody.

04:39.801 --> 04:42.804
- I know.
We're still working the case.

04:42.847 --> 04:44.936
- I get that, but, given
what's happening with Burgess,

04:44.980 --> 04:47.591
I'm gonna have to hand it off
to another unit.

04:47.635 --> 04:49.941
Your team is distracted.
You want to be here with Kim.

04:49.985 --> 04:53.336
You should be--
- No, Sam, we got this.

04:53.380 --> 04:55.991
- We need to arrest Roy fast,

04:56.034 --> 04:57.819
'cause I cannot stand
another minute--

04:57.862 --> 05:00.343
- Sorry for the interruption.

05:00.387 --> 05:02.824
CPIC found Roy's SUV
on a traffic cam

05:02.867 --> 05:05.783
near a warehouse
on the west side.

05:05.827 --> 05:09.439
Even better, somebody reported
hearing gunshots

05:09.483 --> 05:11.441
near that warehouse
earlier tonight.

05:11.485 --> 05:13.095
So who knows?
Maybe we got lucky

05:13.138 --> 05:15.619
and somebody shot this prick.

05:15.663 --> 05:18.579
- That's good.
Thanks, Trudy.

05:18.622 --> 05:21.538
Sam, we're staying
on this case.

05:21.582 --> 05:24.106
It's ours, no one else's.

05:24.149 --> 05:26.717
♪

05:26.761 --> 05:28.806
All right, listen up.

05:28.850 --> 05:32.984
Roy's SUV was clocked outside
a warehouse at 3:00 p.m.

05:33.028 --> 05:34.899
No camera shows it ever left.

05:34.943 --> 05:38.381
911 call of shots fired
came in at 9:12 p.m.,

05:38.425 --> 05:41.602
same location.
We're crashing it now.

05:41.645 --> 05:44.518
- Boss, I need to stay
with Kim.

05:45.475 --> 05:47.390
- Yeah, you're right.
You stay.

05:47.434 --> 05:49.392
- Yeah.
- Let's move.

05:49.436 --> 05:52.395
[tense music]

05:52.439 --> 05:59.489
♪

06:00.185 --> 06:02.840
Jay, you cover the front.

06:02.884 --> 06:04.625
- What are we doing?
- Stop.

06:04.668 --> 06:06.017
- What the hell are we doing?

06:06.061 --> 06:08.672
- We are following a lead,
as simple as that.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.848
You just gotta do your job
like any other day,

06:10.892 --> 06:13.416
any other case.

06:13.460 --> 06:16.463
Chicago PD!
- [grunts]

06:16.506 --> 06:19.466
[dramatic music]

06:19.509 --> 06:26.560
♪

06:52.760 --> 06:54.718
- All right, we're clear.
Let them in, Kev.

06:54.762 --> 06:56.851
- Copy that.

06:56.894 --> 07:03.945
♪

07:10.168 --> 07:11.779
No blood, no body.

07:11.822 --> 07:13.737
Doesn't look
like a crime scene to me.

07:13.781 --> 07:16.479
- Well, we got Roy's SUV.

07:16.523 --> 07:19.874
Maybe the shots were unrelated?
It's weird.

07:19.917 --> 07:21.441
- All right, let's do
a quick search,

07:21.484 --> 07:23.791
then we'll run the perimeter.
Let's go.

07:33.757 --> 07:37.021
Work the scene.
We need your DNA in here.

07:51.775 --> 07:55.823
♪

07:57.607 --> 07:59.914
- There's zero security cameras
in the vicinity.

07:59.957 --> 08:02.220
I don't think we're gonna find
anything private nearby either.

08:02.264 --> 08:03.787
- No doorbell cam.

08:03.831 --> 08:05.049
It must've been
the nearest traffic cam

08:05.093 --> 08:06.137
that picked up Roy's SUV.

08:06.181 --> 08:07.922
- Well,
that doesn't make sense.

08:07.965 --> 08:09.967
When the 911 caller reported
the shots fired,

08:10.011 --> 08:11.752
they practically indicated
the warehouse.

08:11.795 --> 08:13.493
- Hell, the shots
could've come from

08:13.536 --> 08:15.103
any residence in
the neighborhood.

08:15.146 --> 08:16.974
- We got Roy's SUV right here.

08:17.018 --> 08:19.020
So where did he just disappear
to all of a sudden

08:19.063 --> 08:20.848
and how if we've got
the streets shut down?

08:20.891 --> 08:22.893
- Well, let's--let's work
with what we've got.

08:22.937 --> 08:25.069
You two get that SUV processed.

08:25.113 --> 08:26.984
Hailey, let's talk
to the witness

08:27.028 --> 08:29.596
who heard the gunshots.
Maybe he saw something too.

08:31.772 --> 08:33.513
- I'm telling you,
I don't really remember.

08:33.556 --> 08:36.124
It was late when I heard them.
- And that's all you heard?

08:36.167 --> 08:38.692
- Yeah, that was all.

08:38.735 --> 08:41.129
- You didn't see anything,
anyone?

08:41.172 --> 08:44.001
- Like I said, it was late.
I looked out my window.

08:44.045 --> 08:45.655
We don't have good lights
around here.

08:45.699 --> 08:47.004
I looked across the street,

08:47.048 --> 08:49.616
I couldn't see nothing
but the car over there.

08:49.659 --> 08:51.835
- There was a car?
Can you describe it?

08:51.879 --> 08:54.229
- Look, I said all this
when I called 911...

08:54.272 --> 08:56.318
which, by the way, took me
like 15 minutes

08:56.361 --> 08:57.667
to get through to someone.

08:57.711 --> 08:59.626
- Can you describe the car?
Make, model?

08:59.669 --> 09:00.757
- You all should
look into that.

09:00.801 --> 09:01.889
You wonder why
crime's going up.

09:01.932 --> 09:04.544
- Can you please
describe the car?

09:04.587 --> 09:07.677
- Really--you're gonna cop
an attitude with me?

09:07.721 --> 09:09.287
I told the lady on the phone.

09:09.331 --> 09:11.028
I told the patrol cops
that came.

09:11.072 --> 09:13.770
- Sir, we're just following up,
that's all.

09:13.814 --> 09:17.557
Please, just tell us
what you saw, too.

09:19.123 --> 09:20.603
- It was a tan car,
like an old Toyota

09:20.647 --> 09:23.606
or something.
It was idling right outside.

09:23.650 --> 09:26.348
Turned its lights off
when it saw me watch.

09:26.391 --> 09:28.219
- You happen to catch
the plate?

09:28.263 --> 09:30.918
- Hell no,
I didn't catch a plate.

09:30.961 --> 09:33.094
- Okay.
Okay.

09:35.270 --> 09:37.620
- Did you know about this car?
- No.

09:37.664 --> 09:40.623
No, I did not.

09:40.667 --> 09:43.626
[tense music]

09:43.670 --> 09:50.720
♪

10:01.644 --> 10:03.907
- Thank you.

10:03.951 --> 10:06.910
[somber music]

10:06.954 --> 10:12.394
♪

10:12.437 --> 10:14.048
- Nurse said
I could sit with her.

10:14.091 --> 10:16.354
- Yeah.

10:16.398 --> 10:18.226
- She seems okay, right?

10:18.269 --> 10:20.358
- She remains
in stable condition,

10:20.402 --> 10:21.708
but she's struggling.

10:21.751 --> 10:25.886
- Doc, please don't
do this again, man.

10:25.929 --> 10:27.931
- The patient--
- Her name is Kim.

10:27.975 --> 10:30.978
- Right.
I'm sorry.

10:35.765 --> 10:39.116
Your friend Kim
has been through hell.

10:39.160 --> 10:42.119
The amount of trauma
and blood loss...

10:43.904 --> 10:46.776
- I just need to know
what to do.

10:46.820 --> 10:48.735
Her family's on the way.

10:48.778 --> 10:50.911
I'm taking care of
her daughter, I mean...

10:50.954 --> 10:52.826
In the event she survives,

10:52.869 --> 10:55.698
what are we--are we talking
about life support?

10:55.742 --> 10:58.658
- It's still too early to tell,

10:58.701 --> 11:01.791
but it is a possibility.

11:01.835 --> 11:03.445
- I appreciate you shootin' me
straight, Doc.

11:03.488 --> 11:05.403
I do.
Thank you.

11:17.720 --> 11:19.417
- Hey, you two.
- Yes, ma'am.

11:19.461 --> 11:21.463
Anything new on Burgess?
- No.

11:21.506 --> 11:24.379
Still stable,
but still nothing.

11:24.422 --> 11:28.339
But I got the vehicle
your 911 caller saw.

11:28.383 --> 11:31.821
Info must've gotten lost
between patrol and your unit.

11:31.865 --> 11:33.170
I took the liberty.

11:33.214 --> 11:35.172
I found it on
the same traffic cam that

11:35.216 --> 11:39.873
clocked Roy's SUV only about
six hours later, 9:15 p.m.

11:39.916 --> 11:42.092
Ran the plate,
belongs to a Mark Irwin.

11:42.136 --> 11:44.007
- Wait, why does
that name sound familiar?

11:44.051 --> 11:46.183
- Mm-hmm, Mark Irwin--he was
on that list of associates

11:46.227 --> 11:47.750
that Upton, Voight,
and Ruzek hit up.

11:47.794 --> 11:50.361
He's got ties to Roy.

11:52.886 --> 11:54.801
Mark Irwin, he's 52.

11:54.844 --> 11:56.498
He's got three priors
for solicitation.

11:56.541 --> 11:59.240
Vice worked him twice on
suspected child trafficking.

11:59.283 --> 12:00.763
10-to-1 odds says this guy

12:00.807 --> 12:02.765
was helping Roy traffic
the girls in his stable.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.724
- Okay, what's the connection
between the two?

12:04.767 --> 12:07.291
- These two were cell mates
for eight months in 2007.

12:07.335 --> 12:08.989
- Right, so that explains
why Mark was

12:09.032 --> 12:10.468
on Roy's list of last-knowns.

12:10.512 --> 12:12.122
They probably lived
with each other

12:12.166 --> 12:14.908
after they got out of prison.
I know you all had that list.

12:14.951 --> 12:17.388
Which one of you guys
checked him out?

12:17.432 --> 12:19.347
- I-I tried to.
- No, he was on my list.

12:19.390 --> 12:20.957
I didn't make contact.

12:21.001 --> 12:22.393
- All right,
well, our best guess is

12:22.437 --> 12:24.004
that Roy reached out somehow.

12:24.047 --> 12:25.483
Mark went to the warehouse,
picked Roy up,

12:25.527 --> 12:27.268
and now he's trying to help him
get out of the city.

12:27.311 --> 12:28.878
- We got a BOLO on his car?

12:28.922 --> 12:31.489
- And an investigative alert.
We contacted ISP.

12:31.533 --> 12:32.664
This guy's not gonna get far.

12:32.708 --> 12:34.014
If we find Mark,
we're gonna find Roy.

12:34.057 --> 12:35.406
- Right, so I say
we just pull up on his house.

12:35.450 --> 12:36.930
He might be dumb enough
to take him home.

12:36.973 --> 12:38.235
Try to hide his ass there.

12:38.279 --> 12:39.323
- I want to get
started on a warrant.

12:39.367 --> 12:42.413
- Do it, then we move.

12:42.457 --> 12:44.894
- Jay.
- Yeah.

12:46.374 --> 12:48.332
- We need to talk now.

12:48.376 --> 12:49.769
I need to understand
what the plan is.

12:49.812 --> 12:51.466
- Hailey, we can't--
- No, if we find Mark,

12:51.509 --> 12:54.338
we both go to jail.
I know you know that.

12:56.863 --> 13:00.170
So you will talk to me.

13:08.439 --> 13:08.613
.

13:08.657 --> 13:11.573
- Voight.

13:11.616 --> 13:12.922
Voight!
- Not here.

13:12.966 --> 13:16.447
Not yet.

13:17.405 --> 13:20.538
Hailey, you gotta
calm down now.

13:20.582 --> 13:22.671
- I'm just trying to understand
what the plan is.

13:22.714 --> 13:24.716
I mean, maybe I'm missing it,
but chasing Mark,

13:24.760 --> 13:26.414
the one person
that can put us away,

13:26.457 --> 13:28.459
doesn't exactly seem like
a genius strategy to me.

13:28.503 --> 13:31.288
- Right, so what's
the alternative?

13:33.203 --> 13:36.641
Ducking the evidence?
Ignoring active leads?

13:36.685 --> 13:38.905
Tipping off Halstead
and Atwater

13:38.948 --> 13:40.602
that we're afraid to find him?

13:40.645 --> 13:42.473
- Mark's seen our faces.

13:42.517 --> 13:44.998
He's the one who told us
where Roy was hiding.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.260
Now we know
he's been to the warehouse.

13:46.303 --> 13:47.652
What if he saw us there?

13:47.696 --> 13:51.004
- Hailey, you have got to
stop this here and now,

13:51.047 --> 13:52.744
unless this is
too much for you

13:52.788 --> 13:55.617
and you want to confess.
If that's the case--

13:55.660 --> 13:57.271
if that's what
you really want,

13:57.314 --> 14:01.188
then you have got to
let me know right now.

14:01.231 --> 14:04.278
- No, I don't want that.
- Okay.

14:04.321 --> 14:06.323
Then you gotta
accept what happened,

14:06.367 --> 14:09.587
no matter how bad it tastes.

14:09.631 --> 14:12.939
- Okay.
I'm good.

14:12.982 --> 14:16.333
[somber music]

14:16.377 --> 14:19.771
♪

14:19.815 --> 14:23.253
[tense music]

14:23.297 --> 14:26.953
- Chicago PD!
- Mark Irwin!

14:26.996 --> 14:28.955
Chicago PD!

14:28.998 --> 14:36.049
♪

14:39.269 --> 14:41.097
- Bedroom's clear.

14:41.141 --> 14:42.969
♪

14:43.012 --> 14:45.319
- Clear.

14:45.362 --> 14:47.538
- It's clear back here too.
The house is empty.

14:47.582 --> 14:52.804
♪

14:52.848 --> 14:55.155
The bedroom is a mess.
It's like he packed up,

14:55.198 --> 14:56.765
threw his clothes everywhere,
and get the hell out of here.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.158
- Well, it makes sense.

14:58.201 --> 14:59.507
All right, let's search
the place,

14:59.550 --> 15:00.769
see what we can find.
- All right.

15:00.812 --> 15:03.685
- Password protected?

15:03.728 --> 15:06.253
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

15:06.296 --> 15:13.347
♪

15:18.874 --> 15:21.790
- Okay, we find any evidence
Roy was here past 24 hours?

15:21.833 --> 15:23.357
- Nothing yet, Sarge.

15:23.400 --> 15:25.446
We're checking on surveillance
cameras, but so far...

15:25.489 --> 15:27.274
- Okay, what about Mark?
Any hits on that BOLO?

15:27.317 --> 15:29.363
- No, sir.
- Financials?

15:29.406 --> 15:31.539
Credit cards, debit cards?
- That's a negative.

15:31.582 --> 15:34.716
- Well, he's out here
somewhere, so let's dig in.

15:34.759 --> 15:36.370
Hey, you got
that seized laptop?

15:36.413 --> 15:37.849
- Yeah, I was just about
to call the techs.

15:37.893 --> 15:38.850
- I'll take care of it.

15:38.894 --> 15:40.287
I'm heading back
to the district.

15:40.330 --> 15:42.071
- No, it's all good, Sarge.
- No, I want you guys

15:42.115 --> 15:44.378
out here on the street,
going door to door,

15:44.421 --> 15:46.728
talking to neighbors.
Maybe somebody saw Roy.

15:46.771 --> 15:47.859
Where is it?
- All right, cool.

15:47.903 --> 15:50.427
It's in the trunk.
- All right.

15:54.388 --> 15:56.825
- I'm worried about Makayla.
I mean, poor kid.

15:58.914 --> 16:01.525
She's already lost one mother.
I mean, she can't...

16:08.271 --> 16:09.490
She keeps asking me about Kim,

16:09.533 --> 16:12.710
and I keep just saying
that she's at work.

16:12.754 --> 16:17.846
But I gotta, mean, tell her
what's going on, right?

16:17.889 --> 16:20.457
- If you think that's best.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.505
- I mean, should I bring her
down here to see Kim?

16:24.548 --> 16:26.159
You know, just in case?

16:26.202 --> 16:28.683
Because I feel like Makayla's
got a right to see her.

16:28.726 --> 16:31.338
You know, and that it might
bring closure in case...

16:32.643 --> 16:35.255
You know?

16:35.298 --> 16:36.560
But it's like
the other part of me,

16:36.604 --> 16:38.301
I want to protect her
from all of this.

16:38.345 --> 16:40.825
She's finally doing good.
She's finally happy.

16:43.480 --> 16:46.266
And I just--I don't know what
Kim would want me to do.

16:46.309 --> 16:49.182
- Hey, Adam...

16:49.225 --> 16:51.488
There is no right
or wrong answer here.

16:53.795 --> 16:56.276
There just isn't.

16:56.319 --> 16:59.279
[somber music]

16:59.322 --> 17:03.892
♪

17:03.935 --> 17:07.635
- Hey, Stevie, how you been?
- Good.

17:07.678 --> 17:09.898
Lost ten pounds.
- Ah, nice.

17:09.941 --> 17:12.248
- Ah, cut out red meat,
muffins.

17:12.292 --> 17:14.598
Came right off, like nothing.

17:14.642 --> 17:16.296
- Appreciate you doing this.

17:16.339 --> 17:19.429
- Not a problem.

17:23.694 --> 17:24.913
What'd you say
the guy's name was?

17:24.956 --> 17:27.350
- Mark Irwin with an I.

17:27.394 --> 17:29.961
[keyboard clacking]

17:41.451 --> 17:44.193
- Hmm, all done.

17:44.237 --> 17:45.542
- That was easy.

17:45.586 --> 17:47.544
- Well, I'm good.
- Huh.

17:48.719 --> 17:50.547
Here you go.
- Hey, please--

17:50.591 --> 17:52.723
- No, hey, I insist.

17:54.464 --> 17:57.337
- After all you done for me?

17:57.380 --> 17:59.600
You stay safe.

18:05.649 --> 18:08.739
[dramatic music]

18:08.783 --> 18:15.833
♪

18:39.335 --> 18:40.989
- Hailey, it's me.
Are you alone?

18:41.032 --> 18:42.773
- I'm with Jay.
We got a hit on Mark's car

18:42.817 --> 18:43.948
a block from a chop shop.

18:43.992 --> 18:45.907
Thinking he's gonna trade
his car out.

18:45.950 --> 18:47.604
- All right, makes sense.

18:47.648 --> 18:49.563
- Jay ran the owner.
He's got priors.

18:49.606 --> 18:52.653
Retagging, PSMV--clearly
he likes to sell stolen cars.

18:52.696 --> 18:54.437
- All right, good,
check it out.

18:55.482 --> 18:59.486
Found a video on
Mark's computer.

18:59.529 --> 19:03.446
It's of two people outside that
warehouse last night, 9:24 p.m.

19:03.490 --> 19:04.882
- Okay.

19:04.926 --> 19:08.277
- The video was
deleted accidentally.

19:08.321 --> 19:10.584
Matter of fact, the whole
hard drive was destroyed,

19:10.627 --> 19:13.413
but if you find this prick,

19:13.456 --> 19:15.415
we need to search him
for a cell phone

19:15.458 --> 19:16.894
and we need to bag it.

19:16.938 --> 19:19.549
- Copy that.

19:19.593 --> 19:20.637
- All good?

19:20.681 --> 19:22.378
- Yeah,
Voight's just checking in.

19:22.422 --> 19:23.901
- Anything new?

19:23.945 --> 19:26.339
- Nah, he sounds annoyed that
we haven't found Roy yet.

19:26.382 --> 19:29.864
- I get it, but we will.
- If we don't?

19:29.907 --> 19:32.475
- He shot Burgess, tortured
and killed Miller's son.

19:32.519 --> 19:35.304
He murdered three little girls.
We're gonna find him.

19:37.611 --> 19:40.701
- If you say so.

19:40.744 --> 19:42.746
- No, been real quiet.

19:42.790 --> 19:45.488
Only person to come in
is my cousin.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.970
- What about this guy?
You seen him?

19:49.013 --> 19:50.798
- Nah, never seen him.

19:50.841 --> 19:52.582
- No other customers all day?

19:52.626 --> 19:54.062
- I wish.

19:54.105 --> 19:56.369
- All right.
Thanks for your time.

20:01.722 --> 20:04.638
Hey, Hailey, it's Mark's car.

20:04.681 --> 20:06.553
Is he in there?
Is he in there?

20:06.596 --> 20:09.382
Where is he?

20:09.425 --> 20:12.385
[tense music]

20:12.428 --> 20:13.560
♪

20:13.603 --> 20:17.433
- Chicago PD!

20:17.477 --> 20:19.087
Hey! Stop!
[tires screech]

20:19.130 --> 20:21.829
[horns honking]

20:21.872 --> 20:23.831
Chicago PD!
Get out of the way.

20:23.874 --> 20:25.398
Chicago PD!
Stop.

20:25.441 --> 20:26.834
- 5021 George,
we're on a foot pursuit.

20:26.877 --> 20:29.315
I'm going east.
- Copy that, 5021 George.

20:29.358 --> 20:36.409
♪

20:49.552 --> 20:51.119
- [yelps]

20:51.162 --> 20:54.340
♪

20:54.383 --> 20:56.646
- You all right?
You all right?

20:56.690 --> 20:58.387
5021 Henry,
on view carjacking.

20:58.431 --> 20:59.867
Offender fleeing southbound
on Damen.

20:59.910 --> 21:02.783
Gray Honda Accord.
Union nine Nora 899.

21:02.826 --> 21:04.785
- 5021 George, be advised
offender is wanted

21:04.828 --> 21:06.700
on harboring a fugitive.
Should be considered armed.

21:06.743 --> 21:09.790
- Copy that, 5021...

21:12.923 --> 21:13.272
.

21:13.315 --> 21:15.404
- Mark hopped into a car
and he took off.

21:15.448 --> 21:16.536
There's no way he can
get too far.

21:16.579 --> 21:17.841
We locked down
a four block radius.

21:17.885 --> 21:18.929
- Was Roy with him?
- He wasn't in the car.

21:18.973 --> 21:20.409
Hopefully he's in the area.

21:20.453 --> 21:21.671
- Have you talked
to the shop owner?

21:21.715 --> 21:23.499
He know anything?
- Now he does.

21:23.543 --> 21:24.544
We threatened him
with jail time.

21:24.587 --> 21:25.936
He said Mark came in

21:25.980 --> 21:27.416
looking for a whole paint job
on his car,

21:27.460 --> 21:28.461
then he went
across the street to wait.

21:28.504 --> 21:31.681
That's when we showed up.
- Mm-hmm.

21:31.725 --> 21:33.944
Where's Hailey?

21:33.988 --> 21:35.990
- I'll go find her.

21:39.776 --> 21:41.778
- [coughs]

21:43.563 --> 21:46.435
- Hailey?

21:46.479 --> 21:49.395
What are you doing back here?
You okay?

21:49.438 --> 21:52.267
- Yeah, I just needed
to catch my breath.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.269
Come on, let's keep moving.

21:54.313 --> 21:56.358
- Hailey--
- I'm fine, Jay, really.

21:56.402 --> 21:59.622
- Hey, how'd Mark get away?

21:59.666 --> 22:01.755
- What?

22:01.798 --> 22:03.713
- You were chasing him and--

22:03.757 --> 22:05.585
I know you're pretty fast
and he's pretty old.

22:05.628 --> 22:08.283
- He was weaving
in and out of cars, Jay.

22:08.327 --> 22:09.763
I lost line of sight.

22:09.806 --> 22:11.504
Next thing I know he's pulling
a woman out of a car.

22:11.547 --> 22:12.766
There were people around.
What'd you want me to do?

22:12.809 --> 22:13.810
Just start shooting at tires?

22:13.854 --> 22:15.421
- Slow down.
I'm just asking ya.

22:15.464 --> 22:17.901
- Sounds like
you're blaming me.

22:17.945 --> 22:20.730
- What the hell is going on?

22:20.774 --> 22:22.602
- I'm sorry.

22:22.645 --> 22:24.734
I'm just thinking
about Kim and...

22:24.778 --> 22:27.607
Miller's son and the girls.

22:27.650 --> 22:30.610
[soft dramatic music]

22:30.653 --> 22:31.785
♪

22:31.828 --> 22:33.613
- Voight's waiting for you
out front.

22:33.656 --> 22:35.310
- Why?
What's he want?

22:35.354 --> 22:36.616
- I don't know.

22:36.659 --> 22:43.666
♪

22:49.585 --> 22:51.500
- Why weren't you on scene
when we rolled up?

22:51.544 --> 22:53.589
- [scoffs]

22:55.635 --> 22:58.812
Sarge, you got the whole team
out here looking for Mark.

22:58.855 --> 23:01.031
Hell, you just told me that
Mark has a video of us,

23:01.075 --> 23:02.946
outside of the warehouse.

23:02.990 --> 23:05.645
Evidence against us.

23:05.688 --> 23:07.473
You can scrub that computer
all you want,

23:07.516 --> 23:08.822
but you and I both know
how hard it is

23:08.865 --> 23:10.867
to delete something these days.

23:10.911 --> 23:15.959
That video exists.
Mark exists and he will talk.

23:16.003 --> 23:18.527
So, what happens when
we find him?

23:21.487 --> 23:24.403
- Look, we can't ignore leads.

23:26.535 --> 23:28.363
Look, Hailey, when
we encounter a problem,

23:28.407 --> 23:30.452
we will take care of it...

23:30.496 --> 23:32.454
then,

23:32.498 --> 23:35.022
when we know what
the actual problem is.

23:53.736 --> 23:56.391
- Hey.
- Look, we got this, Sam.

23:56.435 --> 23:58.915
Don't put yourself
through this, okay?

23:58.959 --> 24:01.875
If we get any information,
then I promise I will tell you.

24:01.918 --> 24:06.401
- No, I need to find him.
I need him in handcuffs, Hank.

24:06.445 --> 24:08.708
Or on the pavement with
a hollow point in his head.

24:08.751 --> 24:11.972
I need this to end.

24:12.015 --> 24:14.888
- Look,
when Justin was killed...

24:14.931 --> 24:15.976
Sam...

24:16.019 --> 24:19.109
I got this--
this noise in my head

24:19.153 --> 24:21.895
and it was really loud.

24:21.938 --> 24:23.505
And I couldn't turn down
the volume,

24:23.549 --> 24:25.159
no matter what I did.

24:25.202 --> 24:28.467
No matter how hard I tried.

24:28.510 --> 24:31.513
- How'd you shut it off?

24:31.557 --> 24:33.820
- I didn't.

24:33.863 --> 24:37.171
I still haven't.

24:37.214 --> 24:40.566
Noise just feels normal now.

24:41.784 --> 24:43.830
- Sarge, got a hit on the BOLO.

24:43.873 --> 24:46.441
The car that Mark stole was
spotted in Humboldt Park.

24:46.485 --> 24:48.661
[dramatic music]

24:48.704 --> 24:50.924
- 21-12, I'm up
and down Ashland.

24:50.967 --> 24:52.621
We've got no visual
on this guy.

24:52.665 --> 24:54.493
- All right, get to Ward
School, throw down the anchor.

24:54.536 --> 24:56.669
- We got 20 patrol cars
flooding the whole district.

24:56.712 --> 24:59.019
There's no way
he's getting past us.

24:59.062 --> 25:03.850
♪

25:03.893 --> 25:06.026
- 5021 Ida, I'm in pursuit.

25:06.069 --> 25:07.941
I got a gray Honda heading
eastbound on Ashland.

25:07.984 --> 25:10.639
Coming out of 4100 block
approaching the 42.

25:10.683 --> 25:13.033
- Copy you, Kev;
we're coming around west.

25:13.076 --> 25:15.209
- Just made a move.
He's going eastbound on Damen.

25:15.252 --> 25:16.776
- Copy you.
We're moving to intercept.

25:16.819 --> 25:23.565
♪

25:26.786 --> 25:29.963
[sirens blare]

25:38.058 --> 25:39.668
- Drop the weapon.

25:39.712 --> 25:41.627
- Don't move.
- [screams]

25:41.670 --> 25:43.585
- 21 Damen.
Shots fired at the police

25:43.629 --> 25:44.978
outside of a building
on Amherst.

25:45.021 --> 25:47.676
- Get these people back now.
- Get back, get back.

25:47.720 --> 25:49.243
- The fugitive just took
a hostage inside the building.

25:49.286 --> 25:50.984
I repeat, we have
a female hostage.

25:51.027 --> 25:52.899
- Hailey and I'll move in here.
Kev, find another way in.

25:52.942 --> 25:54.117
- Okay, what's going on?

25:54.161 --> 25:55.902
- Mark just took
a woman inside, Sarge.

25:55.945 --> 25:56.903
We're moving in now.
- No.

25:56.946 --> 25:58.208
- What do you mean no?
- No.

25:58.252 --> 26:02.691
No, I say we let him settle.
Let him calm down.

26:02.735 --> 26:05.999
It's a better chance
of saving the hostage.

26:06.042 --> 26:08.958
Get some backup out here.
We set up a containment.

26:09.002 --> 26:11.134
Once he's boxed in,
we talk to him.

26:11.178 --> 26:13.659
Convince him to let
the young woman go,

26:13.702 --> 26:17.184
but the only thing that matters
now is saving her life.

26:17.227 --> 26:20.622
You understand me?

26:27.498 --> 26:27.673
.

26:27.716 --> 26:29.588
- We'll use
every available officer

26:29.631 --> 26:30.937
to clear these buildings.

26:30.980 --> 26:32.634
I want our team on
the immediate perimeter.

26:32.678 --> 26:33.896
- So it's just Mark?

26:33.940 --> 26:35.115
He's the one
who took the hostage?

26:35.158 --> 26:36.812
- Correct.
Still no word on Roy.

26:36.856 --> 26:38.422
- We've been checking
on surveillance.

26:38.466 --> 26:39.772
There's no sign of Mark or Roy
together at all.

26:39.815 --> 26:40.990
- Well, he's gonna know
where Roy is.

26:41.034 --> 26:42.296
That's why he's running,
so we're gonna do

26:42.339 --> 26:43.993
everything we can
to end this with him alive.

26:44.037 --> 26:45.778
- Blueprints are coming in
from the city.

26:45.821 --> 26:47.823
The building's empty--it was
foreclosed on five months ago.

26:47.867 --> 26:49.825
- All right, kill any remaining
power to that building.

26:49.869 --> 26:51.871
Jam any cell phones signals.
- Wait.

26:51.914 --> 26:53.655
How do you want to open a line
of communication to Mark?

26:53.699 --> 26:54.787
Wouldn't a cell phone
make it easier?

26:54.830 --> 26:56.615
- I don't want him talking
to the media.

26:56.658 --> 26:57.920
- Well, then get a radio
in there.

26:57.964 --> 26:59.792
Just one straight
direct line to us.

26:59.835 --> 27:02.664
- Listen, I want this quick,
easy, and controlled.

27:02.708 --> 27:04.840
Our best shot
at deescalating this

27:04.884 --> 27:06.537
is physical communication.

27:06.581 --> 27:08.627
Just him and us.
Trust me.

27:08.670 --> 27:09.845
Come on, Hailey,
just you and me.

27:09.889 --> 27:11.891
- Hank...

27:11.934 --> 27:14.415
give him anything he wants.

27:14.458 --> 27:17.026
Just save that woman
and get him to talk.

27:19.159 --> 27:20.639
- What's up?

27:20.682 --> 27:22.031
- I want you
to get on the roof.

27:22.075 --> 27:25.687
You get a line of sight.
Radios are gonna be dark.

27:25.731 --> 27:27.123
If things escalate
and you get a shot,

27:27.167 --> 27:29.038
you take it.
You hear me?

27:29.082 --> 27:31.650
Another innocent woman is
not gonna die because of this.

27:31.693 --> 27:33.173
- All right.

27:33.216 --> 27:40.441
♪

27:45.185 --> 27:46.839
- What are we really gonna do?

27:46.882 --> 27:50.756
- We're gonna save the hostage.
That's the whole plan, Hailey.

27:54.455 --> 27:57.414
[dramatic music]

27:57.458 --> 28:03.725
♪

28:03.769 --> 28:05.901
- Keep patrol back.
One block out,

28:05.945 --> 28:09.731
that's the minimum.
- I want the police chief.

28:09.775 --> 28:11.602
I want to talk to the boss.

28:11.646 --> 28:13.517
- Where is he?

28:13.561 --> 28:15.563
- Window on the second floor.

28:15.606 --> 28:17.739
- I got information.

28:17.783 --> 28:22.439
♪

28:22.483 --> 28:24.920
I want to talk.

28:26.008 --> 28:28.619
I tell you what I know,
then I let her go.

28:30.143 --> 28:34.495
I promise you I'll let her go
as long as I get the boss

28:34.538 --> 28:38.542
and I'm protected.
I give you five minutes.

28:40.153 --> 28:42.938
- Deputy?
Deputy, what are you doing?

28:42.982 --> 28:44.635
- The man has
valuable information.

28:44.679 --> 28:46.768
He wants to speak
to the person in charge.

28:46.812 --> 28:47.987
- I get it.

28:48.030 --> 28:49.728
Voight and Upton
are already inside.

28:49.771 --> 28:51.773
Radios are dark.
There's no communication.

28:51.817 --> 28:53.035
You can't go inside;
it's too dangerous.

28:53.079 --> 28:54.907
- Well, then let's go
in there together.

28:54.950 --> 28:58.258
You and me.

28:58.301 --> 29:00.608
- All due respect,
that's a bad idea.

29:00.651 --> 29:03.176
- Maybe it is, so let's do
our best not to get shot.

29:07.876 --> 29:09.486
- Mark?
- [shrieks]

29:09.530 --> 29:11.967
- We're coming in, Mark.
- I know you two.

29:12.011 --> 29:15.797
- Just so we can talk.
Just relax.

29:15.841 --> 29:17.799
Okay?
We're not coming any closer,

29:17.843 --> 29:19.975
but you gotta calm down.

29:20.019 --> 29:22.108
- I want the media.
I want your boss.

29:22.151 --> 29:24.806
I want everyone to hear
everything I got to say.

29:24.850 --> 29:28.854
- Okay, that's okay.
We can talk about all of that,

29:28.897 --> 29:31.508
but not when you got a gun
to that woman's head.

29:31.552 --> 29:32.727
Okay?

29:32.771 --> 29:34.250
Now you gotta let her
come to me now.

29:34.294 --> 29:37.210
- You think I'm an idiot?
Bring me the media now.

29:37.253 --> 29:40.213
- Whoa, whoa.
Listen, listen, I get it.

29:40.256 --> 29:41.780
You want to tell your story.

29:41.823 --> 29:43.303
You want the information
out there

29:43.346 --> 29:45.827
and you want to be set free.
I can make that happen.

29:45.871 --> 29:49.613
Okay?
I can do you one better.

29:49.657 --> 29:53.008
I'll tell the whole world
what happened.

29:53.052 --> 29:56.925
You let her go and I will
tell everyone everything.

29:56.969 --> 29:58.709
Okay?

29:58.753 --> 30:00.233
It's got nothing to do
with her.

30:00.276 --> 30:02.670
It's me, him, and you.
That's it.

30:02.713 --> 30:09.764
♪

30:17.772 --> 30:19.339
Just let her go.

30:19.382 --> 30:21.036
Let her go
and I will get you a deal.

30:21.080 --> 30:23.865
- You think I believe you?
- Mark, I promise you--

30:23.909 --> 30:26.868
- You come any closer,
I'll shoot this bitch.

30:26.912 --> 30:28.261
I'll shoot you.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

30:28.304 --> 30:29.915
- I'm not dying here.
- You won't.

30:29.958 --> 30:31.046
We'll work this out.

30:31.090 --> 30:32.961
- [yelps]

30:33.005 --> 30:35.877
- It's okay.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.879
- [strained breathing]
- No, no!

30:37.923 --> 30:39.881
♪

30:39.925 --> 30:42.144
- You're okay, you're okay.
Come on.

30:42.188 --> 30:48.934
♪

30:50.370 --> 30:52.938
Chicago PD!

30:55.766 --> 30:57.116
5021 David.
- No, no, no, no, no, no.

30:57.159 --> 30:59.074
- Shots fired by the police.
I got one down.

30:59.118 --> 31:01.642
Give me an ambo right now.

31:01.685 --> 31:04.863
- Where's Roy?
Where'd you take him?

31:06.038 --> 31:07.996
He's got a pulse.
He can still make it.

31:08.040 --> 31:10.912
Where's Roy, Mark?
Tell me where he is.

31:10.956 --> 31:18.006
♪

31:20.443 --> 31:21.923
- This is car two.

31:21.967 --> 31:24.186
I need a hospital detail
to Med.

31:24.230 --> 31:26.014
I want every street cleared
and shut down now.

31:26.058 --> 31:27.929
- Copy that.

31:27.973 --> 31:33.717
♪

31:38.505 --> 31:38.679
.

31:38.722 --> 31:40.811
- Oh, you're right.
Pink is my color.

31:43.249 --> 31:44.728
Hey, Mak,

31:44.772 --> 31:48.254
I want to talk to you about Kim
real quick, okay?

31:48.297 --> 31:50.430
- Okay.

31:50.473 --> 31:52.301
[somber music]

31:52.345 --> 31:55.174
- So, listen the reason
that she hasn't been here

31:55.217 --> 31:56.827
is she got hurt at work.

31:56.871 --> 31:59.830
- She's hurt?

31:59.874 --> 32:01.658
- Yeah,
but she's in the hospital

32:01.702 --> 32:04.792
trying really hard
to get better.

32:06.011 --> 32:07.447
And listen, kid, the thing is,

32:07.490 --> 32:09.492
is seeing the people you know
at the hospital,

32:09.536 --> 32:10.841
it can be kind of scary.

32:10.885 --> 32:12.234
So I don't really know
if I should

32:12.278 --> 32:13.844
bring you there to see her.

32:13.888 --> 32:17.413
- But I want to see her.
She's my best friend.

32:17.457 --> 32:20.634
She'd want to see me.

32:20.677 --> 32:22.766
- Well, she most
certainly would.

32:22.810 --> 32:26.553
Okay, so go get your jacket.
Let's go see her.

32:26.596 --> 32:31.993
♪

32:32.037 --> 32:34.343
- Gunshot victim.
GSW to the throat.

32:34.387 --> 32:37.303
Pulse shallow but steady.
- Get him into Baghdad.

32:37.346 --> 32:40.306
[dramatic music]

32:40.349 --> 32:43.700
♪

32:43.744 --> 32:45.528
- Two, three.

32:45.572 --> 32:52.579
♪

33:34.621 --> 33:36.275
- He's gone.

33:54.684 --> 33:57.426
- Hey, come here.

33:57.470 --> 33:59.776
- Ladies first.

33:59.820 --> 34:02.301
- Hi.
- Hi.

34:02.344 --> 34:05.434
You look so pretty.

34:05.478 --> 34:08.437
- Thank you.
- Yes.

34:08.481 --> 34:10.787
- Mak brought you something.
Didn't you?

34:10.831 --> 34:13.660
- I brought my platypus
for you.

34:13.703 --> 34:14.835
♪

34:14.878 --> 34:17.098
- [whispering]
He's your favorite.

34:17.142 --> 34:20.493
Thank you.

34:33.071 --> 34:35.464
- Hank.
Hank!

34:35.508 --> 34:36.813
Tell me you got something else.

34:36.857 --> 34:38.467
Tell me we got
a different lead on Roy.

34:38.511 --> 34:39.686
We saw his car,
his ATM card.

34:39.729 --> 34:41.949
- We don't have any leads, Sam.

34:41.992 --> 34:44.125
Doesn't look like Roy
was with Mark.

34:44.169 --> 34:47.128
I mean, not in
the last six hours anyway.

34:47.172 --> 34:50.305
Our best guess

34:50.349 --> 34:53.134
is Mark helped Roy get
out of town late last night

34:53.178 --> 34:55.136
before we caught wind
of his involvement.

34:55.180 --> 34:56.616
- Okay.

34:56.659 --> 34:58.618
Okay, well, then we start
back from zero.

34:58.661 --> 35:00.707
Retrace his steps.
Hit every LKA.

35:00.750 --> 35:03.797
- We already did all of that.
- Well, then hit them again.

35:03.840 --> 35:05.842
We're finding
this son of a bitch.

35:05.886 --> 35:10.760
- Okay, well, I can start back
over if that's what you want,

35:10.804 --> 35:15.548
but we got new cases, Sam.
Cases we can solve.

35:18.725 --> 35:21.858
- I'll call the feds.
Maybe they can help.

35:21.902 --> 35:28.735
♪

35:28.778 --> 35:31.390
- Hey.

35:32.869 --> 35:36.482
Welcome back.
How do you feel?

35:37.961 --> 35:40.747
- Did you find him?

35:40.790 --> 35:42.705
- What?

35:42.749 --> 35:46.666
- I couldn't ask Ruzek,
not with Makayla in the room.

35:46.709 --> 35:50.191
Did you find Roy?

35:50.235 --> 35:53.194
[tense music]

35:53.238 --> 35:58.721
♪

35:58.765 --> 36:01.159
- No.

36:01.202 --> 36:04.771
No, Kim, we didn't.

36:11.169 --> 36:13.562
- Hey.

36:15.956 --> 36:19.089
You had us going for a while.

36:19.133 --> 36:20.874
- You look better
than you probably feel.

36:20.917 --> 36:23.746
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

36:23.790 --> 36:27.141
[indistinct chatter]

36:32.799 --> 36:35.889
- Hey.

36:35.932 --> 36:38.718
Great news about Kim.
- Yeah.

36:41.199 --> 36:43.723
This case is closed.

36:43.766 --> 36:46.595
And we're done.
It's over.

36:46.639 --> 36:49.468
Miller called in the feds
and they'll--

36:49.511 --> 36:52.471
they'll put his face on a wall.

36:52.514 --> 36:55.996
Monitor his ID, credit cards.

36:57.215 --> 37:00.000
But they will never see
or hear a thing.

37:01.784 --> 37:04.613
- Like it never happened.
- That's exactly right.

37:05.788 --> 37:08.226
And now you--

37:08.269 --> 37:12.534
now you got to make peace
with the fact that...

37:12.578 --> 37:16.277
you're never gonna
be able to make peace.

37:16.321 --> 37:20.150
You know what I'm saying?

37:20.194 --> 37:23.153
- Yeah.

37:23.197 --> 37:24.807
I'll do my best.

37:24.851 --> 37:27.245
- They're where they belong.

37:27.288 --> 37:30.857
And after everything Roy did,

37:30.900 --> 37:34.208
I'm not sorry about that.

37:37.080 --> 37:40.127
You saved me.

37:40.170 --> 37:42.608
Let that be enough.

37:48.048 --> 37:50.746
Okay?

38:03.803 --> 38:05.979
- Hey.

38:06.022 --> 38:09.504
- Hey.
Did you get to see her?

38:09.548 --> 38:12.681
- Yeah, I think right
after you and Ruzek left.

38:14.248 --> 38:17.251
She looks good.
- Yeah.

38:28.088 --> 38:30.612
Why'd you propose?

38:35.835 --> 38:39.012
- Because I wanna be with you.

38:39.055 --> 38:42.102
I want us.

38:42.145 --> 38:43.799
I want to know
that I can have normalcy

38:43.843 --> 38:46.715
and stability in my life.

38:46.759 --> 38:48.978
That no matter
how bad things feel,

38:49.022 --> 38:50.632
at the end of the day,
I know they'll be okay

38:50.676 --> 38:52.373
because I'll have you.

38:52.417 --> 38:57.160
- Are you sure
that it wasn't just Kim?

38:57.204 --> 39:00.207
You saw what happened to her--
- I don't know.

39:01.948 --> 39:03.819
Maybe.

39:03.863 --> 39:06.300
[soft dramatic music]

39:06.344 --> 39:10.304
But why does that matter?

39:10.348 --> 39:12.959
I love you...

39:13.002 --> 39:16.876
more than
I ever thought possible.

39:16.919 --> 39:19.574
And maybe it took

39:19.618 --> 39:23.099
Kim getting shot to give me
the courage to tell you that.

39:23.143 --> 39:26.276
♪

39:26.320 --> 39:29.149
I don't know.
- Yes.

39:29.192 --> 39:32.152
- What?

39:32.195 --> 39:39.246
♪

39:45.034 --> 39:47.210
- I love you.

39:47.254 --> 39:49.691
[gentle music]

39:49.735 --> 39:53.391
And I've known since--

39:55.001 --> 39:57.307
I've known for years
that I want it

39:57.351 --> 40:01.660
to be you and me always.

40:01.703 --> 40:08.754
♪

40:11.844 --> 40:15.325
Hailey, will you marry me?

40:15.369 --> 40:16.631
- You don't have to do that.

40:16.675 --> 40:19.286
I already did
the proposal part.

40:19.329 --> 40:22.202
- Well, I'm old-fashioned,
okay?

40:22.245 --> 40:24.770
- [laughs]

40:24.813 --> 40:26.685
♪

40:26.728 --> 40:29.470
Yes.

40:29.514 --> 40:32.995
Yes, I will.

40:33.039 --> 40:40.089
♪

40:47.488 --> 40:47.880
.

40:47.923 --> 40:50.796
[dramatic music]

40:50.839 --> 40:57.890
♪

41:17.083 --> 41:20.129
[wolf howls]
